Reports signature issues for built-in functions.
<p>The inspection will report a wrong number of arguments, invalid keywords, wrong data types, and other issues.</p>
<p>Example (MySQL):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE foo (a INT, b INT, c INT)

SELECT IFNULL() FROM foo; -- error
SELECT IFNULL(a) FROM foo; -- error
SELECT IFNULL(a, b) FROM foo; -- OK
SELECT IFNULL(a, b, c) FROM foo; -- error</code></pre>
<p>In MySQL, the <code>IFNULL()</code> function accepts strictly two arguments. So, only the <code>SELECT IFNULL(a, b) FROM foo;</code>
  query is correct.</p>
